org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.json.jackson

Class JacksonItemDocument

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.json.jackson.JacksonTermedDocument
      • org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.json.jackson.JacksonItemDocument
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EntityDocument, ItemDocument, TermedDocument

    public class JacksonItemDocument
extends JacksonTermedDocument
implements ItemDocument
    Jackson implementation of ItemDocument. Like all Jackson objects, it is not technically immutable, but it is strongly recommended to treat it as such in all contexts: the setters are for Jackson; never call them in your code.
    Author:
    Fredo Erxleben

      • setJsonClaims

        public void setJsonClaims(Map<String,List<JacksonStatement>> claims)
        Sets the "claims" to the given value. Only for use by Jackson during deserialization.

        The name refers to the JSON model, where claims are similar to statement groups. This should not be confused with claims as used in the WDTK data model. This will probably only be used by the Jacksons' ObjectMapper.

        Parameters:
        claims -

      • getJsonClaims

        public Map<String,List<JacksonStatement>> getJsonClaims()
        Returns the "claims". Only used by Jackson.

        JSON "claims" correspond to statement groups in the WDTK model. You should use getStatementGroups() to obtain this data.

        Returns:
        map of statement groups
